A man has pleaded guilty to stealing trees from Nairobi National Park. Samuel Gicheru admitted the charges before Kibera senior principal magistrate Esther Boke. He is accused of cutting acacia trees on January 14 along the Southern Bypass. According to the prosecution, Gicheru was arrested by the officers who were on patrol. “The officers spotted him cutting down trees and he was ordered to stop what he was doing as he was illegally in the protected area,” the court heard. He told the court he was remorseful, but he is poor and is a family man. Gicheru was fined Sh10,000 or serve six months in jail.